
           ####### NSC informational message #######

This is an OpenMP capable MPI-parallel application. By default we are setting
OMP_NUM_THREADS=1 when loading this module to avoid accidental oversubscription
of CPU resources in your job.

If you want to run this installation of Quantum ESPRESSO in MPI + OpenMP mode,
you will need to adjust the OMP_NUM_THREADS value to agree with your SLURM
allocation '-c' value *after* you load this module.

For instance, if your SLURM allocation was made with '-n 32 -c 2', you need to
put

	module load QuantumESPRESSO/7.1-nsc1-intel-2018b-eb
	export OMP_NUM_THREADS=2

in your batch job script. You can go one step further with

	module load QuantumESPRESSO/7.1-nsc1-intel-2018b-eb
	export OMP_NUM_THREADS=${SLURM_CPUS_PER_TASK:=1}

This will set OMP_NUM_THREADS correctly in a SLURM allocation whether you use
the '-c' flag or not (provided you use the bash shell).

HPC_NOTE: hpc_container_exec running container el7 with the following executable:
HPC_NOTE:   /software/sse/manual/QuantumESPRESSO/7.1/nsc1/bin/pw.x -nk 2 -in TiAlN_scf.in

